msgctxt "dn2:0.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 2 "
msgstr "Long Discourses 2 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn2:0.2"
msgid "Sāmaññaphalasutta "
msgstr "The Fruits of the Ascetic Life "

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn2:0.3"
msgid "1. Rājāmaccakathā "
msgstr "1. A Discussion With the King’s Ministers "

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-cs1, pts-vp-pli1.47, sc1
msgctxt "dn2:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "dn2:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati jīvakassa komārabhaccassa ambavane mahatā bhikkhusaṅghena saddhiṃ aḍḍhateḷasehi bhikkhusatehi. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha in the Mango Grove of Jīvaka Komārabhacca, together with a large Saṅgha of 1,250 mendicants. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn2:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto tadahuposathe pannarase komudiyā cātumāsiniyā puṇṇāya puṇṇamāya rattiyā rājāmaccaparivuto uparipāsādavaragato nisinno hoti. "
msgstr "Now, at that time it was the sabbath—the Komudi full moon on the fifteenth day of the fourth month—and King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha was sitting upstairs in the stilt longhouse surrounded by his ministers. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn2:1.4"
msgid "Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto tadahuposathe udānaṃ udānesi: "
msgstr "Then Ajātasattu was inspired to exclaim, "

# NOTE: While these terms may be translated differently according to context, BB’s pasadika = “tranquil” is incorrect; it is part of a stock list of terms meaning “beautiful, attractive”. AN 4.85, etc. Lakkhanna as “auspicious” is also questionable. It is apparently unique in the EBTs. Whereas it may have this sense, following the principle of least meaning I take as not introducing a new theme of “auspiciousness “but as reinforcing the previous terms, i.e.” possesses memorable and remarkable features, i.e. outstanding or striking”.
msgctxt "dn2:1.5"
msgid "“ramaṇīyā vata bho dosinā ratti, abhirūpā vata bho dosinā ratti, dassanīyā vata bho dosinā ratti, pāsādikā vata bho dosinā ratti, lakkhaññā vata bho dosinā ratti. "
msgstr "“Oh, sirs, this moonlit night is so very delightful, so beautiful, so glorious, so lovely, so striking. "

# NOTE: For this setting, compare AN 5.50. BB has “Is there any recluse or brahmin that we could visit tonight who might be able to bring peace to my mind”. However this removes agency from the king to the ascetic. It is not that the ascetic has some special power, but that the King’s act allows him to find redemption.
msgctxt "dn2:1.6"
msgid "Kaṃ nu khvajja samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā payirupāseyyāma, yaṃ no payirupāsato cittaṃ pasīdeyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Now, what ascetic or brahmin might I pay homage to today, paying homage to whom my mind might find peace?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2, sc2
msgctxt "dn2:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro rājāmacco rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ ajātasattuṃ vedehiputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, one of the king’s ministers said to him, "

msgctxt "dn2:2.2"
msgid "“ayaṃ, deva, pūraṇo kassapo saṅghī ceva gaṇī ca gaṇācariyo ca ñāto yasassī titthakaro sādhusammato bahujanassa rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto. "
msgstr "“Sire, Pūraṇa Kassapa leads an order and a community, and teaches a community. He’s a well-known and famous religious founder, regarded as holy by many people. He is of long standing, long gone forth; he is advanced in years and has reached the final stage of life. "

msgctxt "dn2:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ devo pūraṇaṃ kassapaṃ payirupāsatu. "
msgstr "Let Your Majesty pay homage to him. "

msgctxt "dn2:2.4"
msgid "Appeva nāma devassa pūraṇaṃ kassapaṃ payirupāsato cittaṃ pasīdeyyā”ti. "
msgstr "Hopefully in so doing your mind will find peace.” "

msgctxt "dn2:2.5"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto tuṇhī ahosi. "
msgstr "But when he had spoken, the king remained silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3, pts-vp-pli1.48, sc3
msgctxt "dn2:3.1"
msgid "Aññataropi kho rājāmacco rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ ajātasattuṃ vedehiputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Another of the king’s ministers said to him, "

msgctxt "dn2:3.2"
msgid "“ayaṃ, deva, makkhali gosālo saṅghī ceva gaṇī ca gaṇācariyo ca ñāto yasassī titthakaro sādhusammato bahujanassa rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto. "
msgstr "“Sire, Makkhali Gosāla leads an order and a community, and teaches a community. He’s a well-known and famous religious founder, regarded as holy by many people. He is of long standing, long gone forth; he is advanced in years and has reached the final stage of life. "

msgctxt "dn2:3.3"
msgid "Taṃ devo makkhaliṃ gosālaṃ payirupāsatu. "
msgstr "Let Your Majesty pay homage to him. "

msgctxt "dn2:3.4"
msgid "Appeva nāma devassa makkhaliṃ gosālaṃ payirupāsato cittaṃ pasīdeyyā”ti. "
msgstr "Hopefully in so doing your mind will find peace.” "

msgctxt "dn2:3.5"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto tuṇhī ahosi. "
msgstr "But when he had spoken, the king remained silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs4, sc4
msgctxt "dn2:4.1"
msgid "Aññataropi kho rājāmacco rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ ajātasattuṃ vedehiputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Another of the king’s ministers said to him, "

msgctxt "dn2:4.2"
msgid "“ayaṃ, deva, ajito kesakambalo saṅghī ceva gaṇī ca gaṇācariyo ca ñāto yasassī titthakaro sādhusammato bahujanassa rattaññū cirapabbajito addhagato vayoanuppatto. "
msgstr "“Sire, Ajita Kesakambala leads an order and a community, and teaches a community. He’s a well-known and famous religious founder, regarded as holy by many people. He is of long standing, long gone forth; he is advanced in years and has reached the final stage of life. "

msgctxt "dn2:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ devo ajitaṃ kesakambalaṃ payirupāsatu. "
msgstr "Let Your Majesty pay homage to him. "

msgctxt "dn2:4.4"
